OL,3,CJersey schools saw 13 exclusions for
OL,4,C'offensive weapon' cases in 2024
OL,6,FMeanwhile, suspensions due to racist
OL,7,Fabuse have almost tripled since 2020,
OL,8,Frising from 10 in the academic year of
OL,9,F2020-2021 to 27 in 2024-2025.
OL,11,FPersistent disruptive behaviour was
OL,12,Fthe most common cause of exclusions,
OL,13,Fleading to hundreds of pupil removals
OL,14,Fin Grainville, Le Rocquier and Haute
OL,15,FVallee secondary schools.
OL,17,FVerbal abuse of adults, assaults
OL,18,Fagainst both pupils and adults, as
OL,19,Fwell as threatening behaviour, were
OL,20,Falso among the most frequent causes of
OL,21,Fexclusion.
