OL,3,CJersey schools saw 13 exclusions for
OL,4,C'offensive weapon' cases in 2024
OL,6,FPhil Walker, Interim Head of Inclusion
OL,7,Ffor Jersey's Children, Young People,
OL,8,FEducation and Skills department
OL,9,F(CYPES), says: "We don't want assaults
OL,10,Fin schools at all, pupil on pupil, or
OL,11,Fpupil on adult. It's something we've
OL,12,Fworked hard on.
OL,14,F"I'm new to the department but I know
OL,15,Ffrom other head teachers that there's
OL,16,Fa lot of training that's gone on over
OL,17,Fthe last five years.
OL,19,F"There's a lot of work looking at how
OL,20,Fwe move forward with positive
OL,21,Fbehaviour."
