OL,3,CJersey schools saw 13 exclusions for
OL,4,C'offensive weapon' cases in 2024
OL,6,FMr Walker adds: "There were over 10
OL,7,Fmillion school days in the last five
OL,8,Fyears, and only 0.057% of them were
OL,9,Fmissed because of exclusions.
OL,11,F"Around 7% of children have been
OL,12,Fexcluded - that means that 93% of
OL,13,Fchildren and young people in schools
OL,14,Fare showing really positive behaviour."
OL,16,FExclusions were far more common in
OL,17,FJersey's secondary schools than in
OL,18,Fprimary education.
